A '''cool warehouse''' or '''cold storage warehouse''' is a [[warehouse]] were [[perishable|perishable goods]] are stored and [[Refrigeration|refrigerated]]. Products stored can be, amongst other things, [[food]], especially [[meat]], other [[agriculture|agricultural products]], [[pharmaceutical drug]]s, other [[chemical substance|chemicals]] and [[blood]].<ref>{{Cite journal|date=1916|title=New Jersey: Foodstuffs. Cold Storage. Regulation of. (Ch. 101, Act Mar. 16, 1916)|journal= Public Health Reports|volume=31|issue=31|pages=2122–2124|jstor=4573937}}</ref><ref>{{Cite journal|last=Holmes|first=George K.|date=1913|title=Prevention of Waste and Seasonal Price Fluctuations Through Refrigeration|journal=The Annals of the American Academy of Political and Social Science|volume=50|pages=48–56|jstor=1012671}}</ref>
