{{Main|History of hard disk drives#Manufacturing history}} [[File:Diagram of Hard Disk Drive Manufacturer Consolidation.svg|thumb|300px|Diagram of consolidation]]
At least 221 companies were '''hard disk drive manufacturers''' in the past.<ref name="Maleval"/> Most of that industry has vanished through [[bankruptcy]] or [[mergers and acquisitions]]. None of the first four entrants continue in the industry today.<ref name="Informics"/> As shown in the graphic surviving manufacturers are [[Seagate Technology|Seagate]], [[Toshiba]] and [[Western Digital]] (WD) all of whom grew at least in part through mergers and acquisitions.
